# Lessons Learned — {{PROJECT_NAME}}

> Reusable technical findings discovered while working on this project. Add a lesson when you spend non-trivial time solving something that a future session would benefit from knowing up front.
>
> **Pruning**: if a lesson is specific to a single module, consider moving it to that module's context file (`{module}/CLAUDE.md`) after ~30 days. Keep here only what is cross-cutting or generic.
>
> **Categories below are suggestions** — add or remove sections to match your stack.

## Concurrency

(Thread-safety findings, race conditions discovered, locking patterns that worked or didn't.)

## API / Networking

(Rate limits that bite in practice, retry patterns, auth edge cases, API quirks.)

## SQL / Database

(Query patterns that unexpectedly slow down, indexing discoveries, migration gotchas, transaction scope issues.)

## Configuration

(Environment variables that must be set, non-obvious defaults, config conflicts between environments.)

## Deployment

(Rollout traps, cache invalidation, DNS propagation, versioning mistakes, rollback procedures learned the hard way.)

## Code Patterns

(Generic patterns or anti-patterns in this codebase worth documenting for reuse or avoidance.)

